description.$t: I'm the House of Mews superstar in disguise, Harlow!! As you can see I am a beautiful long-haired, tortoiseshell girl and I know it! I'm actually a little shy, but I know I'm gorgeous, so I just can't help strutting my stuff everywhere I go. I guess hearing everyone tell me how beautiful I am has even made me a little more outgoing. They don't even mind my crossed eyes (not that it bothers me). In fact, most people tell me they're just part of my charm! I like to play with toys on sticks. I need a little patience to get over my shyness, but I'll be well worth it in the end. Please don't overlook me just because I am a little shy. Come on, haven't you ever dreamed of living with a supermodel?? Here's your chance! Approx. DOB is 5-20-00.

Aren't I beautiful? I'm Eliza, a Seal Point Siamese girl with stunning blue eyes. I'm a shy kitty, but I'm slowly coming out of my shell more and more. If you catch me in a quiet moment I'd be happy to sit with you while you pet me. I also LOVE being brushed and act like a totally different cat while you are brushing me. I kind of roll around and rub my head on whatever is near. You'll see that I'm quite affectionate. Speaking of affection, if you vist House of Mews you might see my boys running around, Dick and Harry. They are so big it's hard to believe they were my kittens once, but it's true! I'd really like a permanent home (preferably with Dick) with a quiet, loving family. Please don't overlook me just because I am shy. Approx. DOB is 12-21-99.

My name is Penny, and aren't I as pretty as a shiny penny? I think so. So my profile says I am "extra large"...some people say I am a little fat, but I prefer "fluffy." I am affectionate and like to be petted, especially on my head and chin. I can be a little sassy too....that's called a PERSONALITY. I want to be the queen of your household and have no problem holding court lounging in a sun patch, on your bed, or, well....anywhere I feel like. I am playful, too. I enjoy a good brushing and won't want you to stop. Won't you come check me out and see if you are the right one for me? Approx. DOB is 6-9-00.

I'm Patches! I am a very sweet, affectionate and curious kitty living it up at The House of Mews with my sister Inky. We are usually where you are too! We are some of the most personable kitties at The House of Mews. We will be one of the first to greet you at the door when you visit the store. I am playful and *love* to be petted and brushed, but a little bit shy at first. I love toys on sticks! It's fun hanging out with my sister, but I think I would like to come home with you more. But for some reason, even with all these great qualities, Inky and I always get overlooked by adopters. Come and meet me today. You will see why each and every volunteer says I have stolen their hearts (whatever that means). Approx. DOB is 4-24-07.

I'm Inky! I am a very sweet and affectionate kitty--even though I might come off as a little shy sometimes. I will be one of the first to greet you at the door at The House of Mews. I am playful and *love* to be petted and brushed. I will rub my head all over your hand, or whatever you are holding, and I'll roll around all over to get your attention. A real lover! I love toys on sticks! But I am also very laid back. I am an easy going cat and can frequently be found just kickin' it watching the antics around me. My sister Patches still lives here with me, so we have a good time together while we wait and hope for new forever homes. For some reason, even with all these great qualities, Patches and I always get overlooked by adopters. Come and meet me today. You will see why each and every volunteer says I have stolen their hearts (whatever that means). Approx. DOB is 4-24-07.

I'm a nice boy named Adrian. I came to the House of Mews with my 3 sisters and 1 brother (Trini, Trudy, Toni and Tansey)--whew--get me out of here! I am a shy, but loving boy who likes affection. I also love to be brushed and petted and I l-o-v-e to play! When you brush me--and eventually stop--I will reach out my paw to get your hand back over here brushing me where it belongs! I also flop onto the ground and won't go anywhere if you keep on brushing me! I am even learning how to like to be picked up, and yes, even cuddled. I started out very shy, but I have come out of my shell a lot. Aren't I good-looking too? Approx. DOB is 03/24/06.

I'm Dick and I am unique because I am at least part Manx with the c-u-t-e-s-t stub tail! Check it out! I am affectionate and love attention, and love to roll around on my back while you pet my tummy. I can be somewhat of a shy cat, but don't worry, I am a lovebug and have made huge strides coming out of my shell since I came to live at The House of Mews... everyone loves me. I have a soft meow and like to give soft head butts. I'll follow you around begging for attention, and I love to be brushed. I'm super playful too and I love a toy on a stick! Oh, and canned food too. My mother Eliza and my brother Harry live here at The House of Mews too! Harry and I love greeting visitors! Approx. DOB is 12-21-00.

I'm Nikki and I am a beautiful long-haired tuxedo cat. Look at that face! I am shy and sweet, and I like to be petted, especially on my head, but not all the time....I do have a life you know! I love to roll all around on your stack of papers, purring, and I look super cute while I'm doing it. I am playful and curious too. I've been at the House of Mews a long time and wonder why no one seems to want to take me home. All you have to do is understand that I need to take it slow and I can't earn your trust overnight. What's so hard about that, I wonder? Approx. DOB is 4-30-99.

I'm Heather, a very petite, sweet girl. I am super cute, but shy. With some patience and lots of love, I know I will be a wonderful friend for you. I was abandoned, so I need reassurance that will never happen again. I like being petted, and especially brushed! I will come seek you out when I am looking for some attention, and am many times near the front door when you come in. I have adorable little meows ("mew!") and a cute little purr. My best friend at the House of Mews, Nekko, passed away from cancer. We loved to be together and see how I took care of him and gave him a bath in our video. Please don't overlook me just because I am a little shy. Oh yeah, I have stomatitis and only have two teeth left, but I can still eat, you know. I am currently on meds twice a day. Approx DOB is 4-19-04.

First off, I have no idea why my name is Bad Boy...I am not a bad boy at all! Someone just gave me that silly name. I am a shy, but loving gray tabby who needs another chance at a nice home. Although I can be cautious, once I warm up to you I enjoy being petted. I especially like my head scratched.... mmmm.... that feels good! I can even be a little playful sometimes. My brother, Big Boy, and I have been at the House of Mews a long time and just want to find a new forever family. Won't you please come check us out? Approx. DOB is 12/16/00.

I'm a beautiful, black long-haired Persian mix. My name is Fluffy, probably because I'm....fluffy! To win my heart, just give me some space and let me come to you on my terms. But don't you worry, I will be all over you in time, but just let me settle in and get comfy, then I'll be back for more and more lovin'. After a while I will sit in your lap while you watch TV or sleep, I like to be petted, will greet you when you come home with meows, and rub on your legs. I LOVE to give you a bath...my humans need to stay clean! I like to perch in a window or in a sunpatch. I sometimes get the evening "kitty crazies" and can be quite playful! Just take it slow and don't violate my personal space with sudden movements. I probably need a home without small children, and although I can co-exist with other cats, my personality will probably shine through best as an only cat. Approx. DOB is 10-9-01.

I'm Tai, a sweet, yet shy, pretty brown and white tabby with long hair and an adorable pink nose. I can often be found curled up in a cozy basket. Aren't I pretty? My previous owners moved and couldn't take me with them, so I am just trying to get over that. I really enjoy being brushed, just please be quiet and gentle. I am a little shy, but with time and lots of love, I will make a wonderful friend for you. I love a treat of canned food too! Please don't overlook me just because I am a little shy. Please come by and see if I am the cat you have been looking for. Approx. DOB is 5-4-03.

breed.$t: Domestic Short Hair - gray and white

description.$t: I'm Hurley--you may think I am a boy because of that boy on that TV show "Lost"--but I am in fact a *very* sweet girl. But I am somewhat lost myself and need to find a new forever home. I was found in a park where people were trying to poison us kitties! I can be a little shy, but curious and friendly, and I CRAVE your attention and love being petted and brushed! When you come visit The House of Mews, you can be sure I will be meowing for your attention and will follow you around after I get it! I am voluptuous and have HUGE eyes. Please give me a second chance and I know we will become best friends. Look at my face....can you resist? Approx. DOB is 9-24-02.

breed.$t: Domestic Short Hair - orange and white

description.$t: I'm Cinderella, a petite orange and white adorable kitty. I am a shy, sweet girl who tries not to let my shyness get in the way of your attention. I like to be petted and brushed, and with time and lots of love and patience, I will make a wonderful friend for you. When you pet me I wriggle around all over and rub my face all over too--not to mention p-u-r-r-i-n-g and a few cute little meows. That means I love it! I love a bit of canned food too and am really cute when I am "asking" for it. I need to be adopted with my best friend forever, Bonita. We can frequently be found curled up together in a basket, like in our picture. She looks a lot like me but we're cousins, so that's not too surprising. She's the only family I have right now since my mom went over the rainbow bridge. I am the lighter colored one, and she is a bit darker orange. Please don't overlook us just because we are shy. Approx DOB is 4/1/03.

breed.$t: Domestic Short Hair - orange and white

description.$t: I'm Bonita, a petite orange and white adorable kitty. I am a very shy kitty who is trying to learn to be petted and let people be nice to me. Hopefully with time, patience and lots of love, I can learn to open up and become more social and make a wonderful friend for you. An interesting fact is although I am still learning to be petted, I love being brushed. I need to be adopted with my best friend forever, Cinderella. We can frequently be found curled up together in a basket, like in our picture. She is tiny like me and looks a lot like me--but we're cousins so that's not too surprising. I am the darker colored one, and she is a bit lighter orange. Please don't overlook us just because we are shy. Please come give us a chance? Approx. DOB is 3/7/03.

I'm Fredo, a very handsome orange tabby. I am a little shy right now, but maybe I just need a nice, loving home of my own to let my personality bloom and blossom. Wait, that sounds too girly.... Well, I am currently residing in living quarters with ALL GIRLS! I actually have opened up a LOT since moving in here and I can be a real love bug. I really love to be brushed and will rub all around your legs while you are brushing me. I am sweet, curious, and I like treats. Anyway, hopefully someone will give me a chance to be a wonderful friend for you. Please don't overlook me just because I am a little shy. Approx. DOB is 2/2/07.

I'm Jessica, a cute petite gray and black tabby. I was abandoned, and because I haven't had a stable home, I am very shy. But surely when I get to know you, I will love you? I require lots of love and attention to come out of my shell, and a special person who is willing to work with fearful kitties and give me a chance. Please don't overlook me because I am shy. PS - I LOVE canned cat food. Approx DOB is 2004.

I am a small, all black kitty, yet I am part siamese. That makes me very sleek and pretty. Isn't Licorice a great name? I am a little shy, but like to be petted and brushed. I like to curl up in the many baskets at the House of Mews, but a basket at your house would be better (no offense to the House of Mews). Please don't overlook me just because I am a little shy. Please come meet me and maybe we'll be a match? Approx. DOB is 10-8-05.

I'm Ansel, a black and white tuxedo cat with beautiful markings, and long white whiskers. I am shy, so I need lots of love and attention to further on my developing personality. I was quite afraid of people when I first came to the House of Mews, but now I get along well with other cats and am working on getting more comfortable around humans. But I think they just call that "aloof" right? I am learning to be petted more and more. I like a good head scratching (especially when canned food or treats are involved--hint hint). I meow-meow-meow when canned food is being served up. I think that with a good home with patient people, I may open up and become a bit more affectionate. I like to play with toys on sticks sometimes too. I enjoy basking in the sun in the front window of the House of Mews. Sometimes I eat and drink with my paw...it's really cute. Approx. DOB is 06/14/99.

I'm Seneca and I C-R-A-V-E your attention! I am a large lovebug who LOVES to be petted and brushed. In fact, when you brush me I go crazy and rub my face all over and roll around--it makes me so happy! I also will roll onto my back and like tummy rubs and will purr, purr, purr! However, I am shy at first, and wary of sudden movements or noises, so as long as you keep that in mind we should be able to be good friends. I have been at the House of Mews a very long time and I think people may overlook me just because I am shy? There is no other reason? I like to eat canned cat food with my paw--it is so cute! On that note, once you adopt me, you are going to *have* to give me a canned food treat every once and a while...it is my favorite thing (well, maybe treats are my favorite thing too). I hope you will come visit me at the House of Mews and see what a lovebug I am! The volunteer who is typing this for me (paws make that kind of difficult) says that I am one of her favorites...even though I don't think she is supposed to have favorites... Approx. DOB is 9/29/98.

I'm Toni, and in a word, can you resist that face? I came to the House of Mews with my four sisters and brothers (Trini, Trudy, Tansey and Adrian). I love to be brushed and petted, and always want to inspect what you are doing. I came to the House of Mews fearful, but I have progressed well and now I am just a little shy. But don't worry--I can even be picked up now and am a real lovebug! I am playful too. I am mostly white, with some black and white tabby spots on the top of head and my tail. Approx. DOB is 2-28-06.

Hi! I'm Trudy. I am a pretty white kitty with large tabby patches on my back and head. I like to be petted and will flop on the floor for more lovin'. I like to talk (meow!) and I like to be brushed, well, most of the time. And I can go crazy batting around a toy, although it may not look like it from my photos. I came to the House of Mews with my 4 brothers and sisters (Trini, Toni, Adrian and Tansey), fearful, but I am sooooo much better now! Don't worry, I like people, I am still just shy in some ways. I like to play too. Won't you please come check me out? Approx. DOB is 2-28-06.

Hi, I'm Trini and I'm a white kitty with small tabby spots on my back and head. I like to be petted and brushed (mmmm....that feels good) and I know it may not look like it from my photos, but I can be playful and can go crazy batting around a toy! I came to the House of Mews with my 4 brothers and sisters (Toni, Trudy, Adrian and Tansey), fearful, but look at me now! I am still shy and cautious, but I have really warmed up to people. You can even pick me up now (I think that's called progress). Look at that face...how can you resist? Approx. DOB is 2-28-06.

They call me Tansey and I am a white cat with tabby spots. I am a very handsome cat but "some people" think cats are supposed to sit in your lap, get petted, and brushed. Well, even though many of my House of Mews roommates go along with that theory, I am my own cat and will do what I please, thank you very much. I am curious and inquisitive (can't you tell from my expression?) but will keep my distance. However, in a quiet moment when I am in a basket, I will allow myself to be petted and I must admit it feels pretty good. I came to the House of Mews, fearful, with my 4 brothers and sisters (Adrian, Trini, Trudy and Toni) and just haven't figured out those silly humans yet. My brothers and sisters have decided they like humans for the most part, and they keep bugging me about it.....siblings! However, some people say that with a loving home, with a special loving and patient person, who is interested in working with fearful kitties, I might learn to open up some and become a bit more affectionate. Who knows? Approx. DOB is 3-24-06.

I'm Little Debbie. I am looking for a new home, and all of my brothers and sisters have been adopted...Hershey, Baby Ruth, Reeses and Sugar Daddy....but why not me? I am a sweet, but a little shy, little girl who is looking for a nice new home. All I need is some extra TLC and I believe I can make a wonderful friend for you. I really enjoy being petted and brushed! I am a curious cat and like to watch what's going on around me at the House of Mews. I love toys on sticks and batting around other toys! Won't you please come visit me and see if I am the right friend for you? Don't worry about my crooked ear...it is endearing, right? Please don't overlook me just because I am a little shy. Approx. DOB is 9-26-05.

My name is Delilah and see what a pretty torbie face I have? My photo doesn't do me justice so I think you need to come see me for yourself. I have beautiful markings! I was found as a stray in a trailer park. I am a very curious and playful cat and like to play with toys on sticks, and have tons of fun batting around soft toys with my paws (oh, it's really cute when I do it too). I will admit I am a shy kitty, but maybe if I find the right home with patient new pet parents and lots of TLC I can learn to come out of my shell more? I am ok with being petted sometimes and sometimes I even like a few brush strokes. But my shyness is just due to the fact that I still need to get to know you so please just understand that I can't earn your trust 100% overnight. Being abandoned can take its toll on a kitty, ya know? Please don't overlook me just because I am shy. Approx. DOB is 10-13-05.

I'm Daisey, a Calico kitty but you can tell me apart from the other Calicos in this place because I have an all-black nose. You may see me around The House of Mews with my sister Poppy, or perhaps taking in the whole scene perched high on the cat walks or in a sunny window. I am a playful and curious kitty and I like toys on sticks. I like to be petted. Please come visit my sister and I today! We are soooo cute and soooo sweet. PS - Poppy and I would like to be adopted together. What is better than one cat? TWO! Approx. DOB is 10/7/06.

Hi, I am a sweet Calico, with beautiful markings, don't you think? You may see me around the House of Mews with my sister Daisey, or perhaps taking in the whole scene perched high on the cat walks or in a sunny window. I like to play and am a curious cat. I like to be petted, especially on my head and chin. I will reach out to you with my paw for attention, then roll over on my back so you can rub my tummy. Please come visit my sister and I today! We are soooo cute and soooo sweet. PS - Daisey and I would like to be adopted together. Approx. DOB is 10-7-06.

I'm Maggie and I am a beautiful gray spotted tabby looking for a special, loving home. You see, when I was a kitten I was left locked in an abandoned house for two weeks before someone found me and let me out! Then I had to live on the streets until I came to live at the House of Mews. Being abandoned like that is no way to start out, so needless to say I am a shy kitty. I am trying to figure out if all humans are "safe" or not since I didn't really know any nice ones in the past. I will rub my head on your ankles when you are serving canned food. Sometimes the House of Mews volunteers can sneak in a few pets... I love canned food and when I smell it I forget that I am still learning how to enjoy petting and affection. Those tricksters! Maybe a special home with patient caregivers, extra TLC and some understanding that I could open up and become more affectionate? Approx. DOB is 9-21-04.

My name is Osha and I am a LOVER and will take any opportunity I can get to hop onto your lap. I love to be petted and love to talk to you while you're at it. Everyone knows who I am at the House of Mews because although there a Iot of black cats that live "loose" in the store, I am the only one that will leap straight into your lap. Sometimes I like to be brushed, but I'd really prefer a good petting. I will be tricky to catch (wouldn't you be?) but I am sure there is someone out there willing to give it a try? Approx. DOB is 2-15-98.

I am Obsidian and I came here to the House of Mews as a kitten with my brother, Onyx, but he already got adopted so it's just me now. I am a handsome black cat looking for a warm and loving new home. I am sweet and loving, but can be a little shy. But I still crave your affection and am a playful cat. But hey look at my pictures--I am such a good cat I tolerate getting dressed up! I am pretty much grown up now but they decided to leave one of my kitten pictures posted too because it is pretty darn cute. I am very curious and always on the move. I can be cradled in your arms like a baby and purr. I also like my tummy rubbed and will roll around on the floor. Approx. DOB is 1-17-08.

Hello, my name's Charlie and I am a very handsome cat. "Some people" think cats are supposed to sit in your lap, get petted, and brushed. Well, even though many of my other roommates go along with that theory, I am my own cat and will do what I please, thank you very much. I am curious and inquisitive (can't you tell from my expression?) but I will keep my distance. I came to the House of Mews as a stray from an apartment building and just haven't figured out those humans yet. HOWEVER, I love treats and will meow if you aren't handing them out fast enough! I'll even let your hand get really close to me as long as there is a treat in it. Maybe someday a very special loving and patient person who is interested in working with fearful kitties will decide to take me home with them and I might learn to open up some and become a bit more affectionate. Who knows? Approx. DOB is 7-9-02.

OK, OK....you may notice that my description says "senior," but all that means is that I am smarter and know more than most of these other cats around here. Pleeeaaaase..... I spend most of my time up near the ceiling on the catwalk watching all the younger cats running around and acting ridiculous. Really, the more dignified cats hang up here with me. I guess I am what some might call "semi-feral" but I just prefer to do my own thing and at my age, I think I have earned that right, thank you very much. I will let you in on a little secret, I do have one weakness, I L-O-V-E treats and canned cat food! In fact, when you are serving either one up, you can hear my distinctive (and loud) meow. Some volunteers at the House of Mews call me "the meower." Most people like to hear their own voice, don't you? Anyway, some people say that with a loving home, with a very special loving and patient person, I might learn to open up some and become a bit more affectionate toward humans (I like other cats just fine). Who knows? Approx. DOB is 5-20-96.

Meow, I'm called Meggie and I am quite petite and have a sleek black coat and big green eyes. I was abandoned in a locked house for two weeks, then when I was freed I was forced to live on the streets! But that was a while ago and thankfully I currently reside safely at the House of Mews where I am in search of a patient and loving person who would like to be my new pet parent. You see, during my past life I didn't receive very much love and affection so I may not be quite as cuddly as some of my other roommates here. But I have warmed up a lot and now I am a sweet kitty and I enjoy being petted and brushed. I'll even ask you for your attention, so you better be ready to give it up when you come visit me at the House of Mews! Maybe with some extra TLC I know I will come out of my shell even more. Please don't overlook me because I am a little shy. I am a sweet (and did I mention pretty?) girl. Approx. DOB is 9/21/04.

breed.$t: Domestic Short Hair - gray and white

description.$t: Hello, my name's Lazuli and I am a small, sleek and spry, gray and white cat. "Some people" think cats are supposed to sit in your lap, get petted, and brushed. Well, even though many of my other roommates go along with that theory, I am my own cat and will do what I please, thank you very much. I am curious and inquisitive and like being in the center of the action, but I will keep my distance. HOWEVER, in a quiet moment when I am in a basket or sitting in a chair, I will allow myself to be petted all over and I must admit it feels pretty good. I came to the House of Mews as a stray (with my mommy, Lake) and just haven't figured out those humans yet. However, in a loving home, with a very special loving and patient person who is interested in working with fearful kitties, I might learn to open up some and become a bit more affectionate. Who knows? Approx. DOB is 4-30-05.

Hi there, my name is Lake and I am a small, black and white tuxedo cat. You can tell me apart from the other tuxedo cats at the House of Mews because I have a white "ring" on one of my otherwise black left back leg, and I also have pretty white whiskers. "Some people" think cats are supposed to sit in your lap, get petted, and brushed. Well, even though many of my other roommates go along with that theory, I am my own cat and will do what I please, thank you very much. I am curious and inquisitive and like to see what's going on, but I will keep my distance. I came to the House of Mews as a stray (with my kitten, Lazuli) and just haven't figured out those humans yet. However, in a loving home, with a very special loving and patient person who is interested in working with fearful kitties, I might learn to open up some and become a bit more affectionate. Who knows? Approx. DOB is 11-30-04.

Hi there, I'm Tux, a black and white tuxedo cat. I have a shy side, so I need lots of love and attention to further on my ever-developing personality. I was quite afraid of people when I first came to the House of Mews, but LOOK AT ME NOW! I will be one of the cats that comes and tries to gain your affection when you walk in the door. I'll rub up against you, hop up on the bench next to you, or into your lap, and I LOVE being petted, especially on my head and chin! I can be picked up and even cuddled a little, as well as I enjoy being brushed. I do that stuff even more if TREATS are involved! When more than one cat is vying for your attention, I like to be first so I will swat the other cat! But I don't hurt 'em or anything. Come on, you can see from my picture that I can be "dressed up" so I must be a good cat if I will tolerate that! Now I am not saying I still don't put on the "aloof" act too, so you just have to be patient and understand that I am still a little shy at heart and I'll probably do better in a quiet environment where there aren't things to scare me. Approx. DOB is 4/26/99.

My name is Apollo and I need a special home. Wait a minute, that sounded like a 12-step program meeting, lets start over. I am a handsome, very large black male cat. I mean, I might be the biggest cat here at the House of Mews! I also have huge yellow eyes that can turn from almond-shape to huge round circles in seconds! I am very curious and inquisitive (why do you think I get those big eyes?). Anyway, I was abandoned (along with my siblings Bach and Aurora) and I guess I was never really socialized around people the way I should have been, and now I am somewhat fearful of people (and loud noises, like vacuums). If you want to pet me you just need to take it slow. Just choose a quiet moment, come on over, and slowly hold your hand out for me to sniff first. Depending on my mood, I sometimes like to be petted on my head and chin, and I even have been brushed a few times. Dont freak out if I hiss at you, its just my way of telling you I am a little scared at first. Would you want someone 10 times your size reaching out for you? Oh, and if you have TREATS, Ill almost always let you pet me...well maybe just a little. However, maybe if a very special loving and patient person comes along, who is interested in working with fearful kitties, I might learn to open up some and become more affectionate. Who knows? Approx. DOB is 04/07/05.

Meow, my caregiver died so now I am in search of a new forever home all over again. I am a shy, sweet and affectionate lapcat. I like my head petted, and I really like it when you scratch me under my chin (and behind my ears too). I am OK with being brushed, and I need it too being that I am a long-haired cat. I am sure with a patient and loving new pet parent, I will come back out of my shell more and become a special companion for you. I have hopes that someone out there may have a special place in their heart for me and a little extra TLC, and give me a second chance. Everyone deserves one, you know... Approx DOB is 9-16-04.

I'm Bessie, a front-declawed black kitty with just a small patch of white on my chest...see the spot? I am a very loving kitty, but am a little shy. I enjoy being petted though and I just have to warm up to you, you know? If you give me canned food I'll be your best friend (no, that's not a bribe). My caregiver lost home to foreclosure and so did I. So now I must look for a new forever home. Purrty please come meet me and see if I am the right match for you. Of course I currently live with a bunch of other cats, but I don't really like them too much. Approx. DOB is 9-26-99.

Meow, I'm Setsuna, a pretty Torbie. Torbie--isn't that a funny word? I am a sweet kitty who enjoys being petted, but am a little on the shy side. Aren't my markings pretty? I like to perch around the House of Mews and survey everything going on around me. And that's a lot! Please give me a chance and don't overlook me just because I am a little shyer than some of the other cats around here. DOB is 10-1-03.

I'm Mandy. If you are looking for an extremely loving and sweet cat, then I may be the right one for you! I love attention and being held. I will P-U-R-R and rub my head on your chin when you cuddle me. But I have a shy side and like to hide a lot to feel safe. As you can see from my picture I frequently will put my paws on your leg and meow to tell you I want to be held and loved. I will lay in your lap on my back and you can rub my tummy. The only other home I have known besides the House of Mews is a garage. Please come meet me soon! I know you're gonna love me! I AM CURRENTLY BEING FOSTERED--CONTACT THE HOUSE OF MEWS IF INTERESTED IN ADOPTING ME. Approx. DOB is 6-24-08.

Hi there, my name is Soho and I am a sleek black cat that also happens to be part Siamese. "Some people" think cats are supposed to sit in your lap, get petted, and brushed. Well, even though many of my other roommates go along with that theory, I am my own cat and will do what I please, thank you very much. I am curious and inquisitive and like to see what's going on, but I will keep my distance. I was abandoned early on in life and have just never figured out those humans yet. However, in a loving home, with a very special loving and patient person who is interested in working with fearful kitties, I might learn to open up some and become a bit more affectionate. Who knows? Approx. DOB is 9-2-03.

I'm Midnight Star, a handsome refined gentleman of a cat. I am shy and haven't really ever gotten 100% comfortable around humans. But I think they just call that "aloof." However, sometimes I like to be petted (just don't approach me too fast or be too loud). I might be a little scared at first. Would you want someone 10 times your size reaching out for you? Sometimes I let my guard down more than other times. As you can see from my photo I am a curious cat and like to spend many hours perched up high surveying the scene around me with my paws hanging down. Approx. DOB is 4-29-00.

I'm Lexie and I lost my home when my caregiver was evicted. Everyone and everything was just thrown into the street, can you believe I was treated like that!?!? Anyway, I am an affectionate cat, but I have a shy side too. I LOVE being brushed - I'll purr and rub my face all over everything, including you. I reach out with my paw to grab you when you stop, along with some hearty meows. I like being petted, especially if you are giving me treats or canned food! And, I know how to open the mail slot with my face and keep it open resting on my nose while I look out into the world. I also am playful in a way and will grab onto your arm, bunny kick you and play bite... once I get to know you that is. Approx. DOB is 4-3-01.

My name is Gwen, named after Gwen Stefani, but I am not all crazy and in your face like she is. I am a sweet and loving black cat, with just the smallest patch of white on my chest. I am gentle and quiet, yet curious, and enjoy affection. I love to be brushed and I'll sit on your lap while you stroke me. I yearn for your love, but since I am a little quiet and shy, don't take it the wrong way if I hide for a little while when you take me home. Trust me, I will love you and want to be friends. I just need a little extra TLC to adjust to a big new place. Please give me a chance, 'cause I kinda get overlooked in here in favor of other cats who may be more forward and up in your business. But I promise I am just as nice a cat as any of them. Approx. DOB is 9-15-08.
Approx. DOB is 5-30-09.

I'm Boots,and I am looking for a forever home. I am a sweet kitty, but am a little on the shy side. I think they call that reserved. I'll just need some extra TLC and patience, you know? I loved my best friend Mr. T who recently went over the rainbow bridge - we were together most of our lives. You could find us sometimes grooming each other and curled up together taking a nap. I left a picture posted of us together in his honor. Oh yeah, if you think one of my eyes looks a little funny, I have a birth defect but it does not affect my vision depth or perception. Please come check me out, and don't overlook me just because I am shy. Approx. DOB is 6-16-03.

Susan is a cute petite Calico cat who was a stray and caught via trap in someone's yard. She gave birth to three kittens (Carl, Markie, and Billy) at The House of Mews. Look at what a good mommy she was (although her mommy days are over now). She is a sweet cat who loves her head scratched. She likes to sit in a basket and roll all around it and rub her head on every square inch. She is sure to make a loving companion for a lucky adopter. She is a little on the shy side sometimes, but probably nothing getting settled into a permanent loving home won't cure. Approx DOB is 9-9-07.

I'm Harry, and I once got adopted from the House of Mews, but found my way back when my elderly pet parent could no longer keep me. And guess what--my brother Dick and my mom Eliza still live here too! It is good to have some family here. I am a loving and curious Manx cat with about a 1/2 to 3/4 of a tail I'd say. I was just born that way. My brother Dick has an even shorter tail. I am playful and will try and earn your affection, and hopefully a little canned food too. I LOVE to be brushed...I will rub my head on you and whatever may be near while you are brushing me. I love head skritches too. I will reach out to you with my paw when you stop petting me, or perhaps when you walk by and I want some pets. Dick and I love greeting visitors at The House of Mews, and we know no strangers! DOB is 12-21-00.

I'm Tizzie but I really don't get in a "tizzy" very often, in fact, I am a rather quiet cat. Well, I guess sometimes I do get a little crazy, if you walk up on me too fast, I may try to run away fast, and I look like those cartoons that run in place for a couple of seconds before I get myself moving. Although I can be a little timid, I am a sweet cat. You can put me on your lap and I will lay down and roll over while you pet me. I LOVE my tummy rubbed too. I like my head scratched and like to sleep in a basket. When you pet me in the basket I roll all around. Um, and I am a littlle, uh, fluffier now that in my picture. Yeah, fluffy, that's it. My kittens Torrence and Taylor are gone and it's just me now. Approx. DOB is 4-3-09.

I was found as a talkative and sweet stray, who always wanted to come inside the house but the person who was feeding me was allergic to cats. I am very affectionate and playful too. I have been told I am intelligent and gentle, and have a great personality. So I guess if someone said it, it must be true. Why don't you come and find out for yourself? Approx. DOB is 4-30-08.

I'm Harley, a purebred neutered front-declawed Silver Maine Coon. Whew, that's a mouthful! Speaking of mouthfuls, I am a talkative kitty, who needed more attention than what I was getting at my previous home. I love to be petted on my head and will head-butt your hand when you stop. I am playful and like toys. I have an independent streak and like some time to myself...you don't have to be up in my business all day and night... sheesh! At the very beginning I may be a little hesitant coming to you, etc. but as soon as I get to know you, I will be asking for petting and will call myself your friend. I might get a little grumpy from time to time, but hey, I bet you do too... I will forgive you if you forgive me. I am loving the rest of the time you know. DOB is 7-27-05.

I am a beautiful little girl, and I have changed a lot since arriving at the House of Mews. When I was a baby I was scared of people... I would even forget my manners and hiss at you! I may still act shy or unsure, but it is totally obvious that I am seeking your affection. You can pet me and I may kind of run away, but then I come RIGHT BACK! I am kind of like a tease, I heard someone say. I will rub my face on stuff while you pet me, which means I like it. I like to be brushed too, and will lurk around hinting if you are brushing other cats instead of me. I will lay down and show you my pretty coat and I dont try and run away or anything while you are admiring me. If you put me on your lap, I may sit there for a little bit while you are petting me, but I think I just need some more warming up before I get too comfortable. I just need a new forever home where they will understand I just need a little extra TLC to make me feel comfortable and loved. Please come meet me and give me a chance. Approx DOB is 4-28-10.

I'm Ms. Toody, an admittedly spoiled diva cat. It is not a coincidence that in one of my pictures I am sleeping in the "princess bed." I guess I need to tell you right off the bat that I do not like small children--that is why my previous caregivers gave me up. I was very unhappy living with their small child, and they had another on the way. I guess I don't really like other cats either... I kind of like my own kitty space. But I love being the center of your attention and like a small treat of wet food after you brush/comb me. Please love me. Did I mention I have a long fluffy coat too? PS - I do not like my tail or my tummy petted. THIS CAT IS BEING FOSTERED. CONTACT THE HOM IF INTERESTED IN ADOPTING. Approx DOB is 2-18-05.
One of eight kittens rescued from a crawlspace. Approx. DOB is 10/4/10.
One of eight kittens rescued from a crawlspace. Approx. DOB is 10/4/10.

I was living outside cold and hungry, when I wandered upon a nice lady's porch. I meowed very loudly so she would hear me and come find me. I was fed and given a warm place to sleep for the night, but alas the lady already had too many cats so I couldn't stay. I am loving and I love to cuddle, and crave your attention. I will sit on your lap, be held, and purr, purr, purr. I like toys on strings. I like to talk to you. Why don't you come test me out for yourself? I am a small, black kitty, but have kind of a unique white/silver undercoat. Approx. DOB is 8/22/10.

Mew, I was found outside someone's door in the cold. They couldn't take care of me, so that's why I live here at the House of Mews now. But they did say this about me: "She loves to roll over and play. She'll talk to you and look at you with loveable eyes. She likes belly rubs. She is friendly but a little wary of strangers at first." Well, obviously I don't talk to strangers, duh! Don't you read the news? I like to be brushed too. Not so sure what I think about the House of Mews just yet and am still trying to get adjusted to this place and all these other cats. It's a big place for a little cat, ya know? Did you see how pretty I was? I bet the other cats in here are jealous. Approx. DOB is 8/5/10.

My previous owner moved and left us cats behind! Hmph! Then another neighbor took me in, but sadly cant afford to keep me. Besides my good looks and long beautiful coat, I am a real sweetie, and was loved very much by the neighbor who took me in. I had kittens on 3-31-11 but they are all adopted so it's just me now (Lobo, Pedro, Lola, Chico, Taco). Approx. DOB is 9/18/09.

Bastet was aptly named after the Egyptian cat goddess. She is a quiet tortie girl who will be your companion and friend without all that kitten craziness. Come down to The House of Mews and meet this beauty today! She has pretty markings and a fluffy tail. Approx. DOB is 8/31/10.

I was rescued from Memphis Animal Services, where I would be put to sleep. I am a sweet, loving kitty. When you enter Penthouse #1, you may not notice me at first as I like to curl up for naps in a basket high above the floor. But once you come and acknowledge me, you will see I am yearning for your affection and love to be petted. I rub my head all over and roll around in the basket. Just because I do not leap all over the penthouse when you enter - like some of my other roommates - doesn't mean I am not just as much of a sweet kitty as they are. You just gotta be sure and seek me out! And any cat that will wear a Santa hat sounds like a pretty good cat if I do say so myself. Approx. DOB is 4-1-10.

Sparkle was pregnant and was rescued from being put to sleep at Memphis Animal Services. She has since had her kittens and is current on vaccinations and microchipped. She is a very sweet cat - you could sit for hours and brush and pet her. And what a pretty cat! Approx. DOB is 4/12/09.

I was abandoned along with my feline friend, Isis. I'm affectionate and you can often find me waiting on the corner of the retail desk, waiting for the "you're beautiful" pat on the head. Every pat on the head might be a pat from my new forever caregiver? So I keep on hoping and maybe the next pat will be "the one." Approx. DOB is 4/23/08.

breed.$t: Domestic Short Hair - orange and white

description.$t: I was found on the University of Memphis campus, under a large metal dumpster when I was a tiny kitten. A hawk was circling above - gulp! But I was rescued by a nice student. Whew! I am now all grown up and a BIG, handsome boy! I will greet you at the door and rub all over your legs and follow you around. I will lay in your lap and purr while you pet me. I also L-O-V-E plastic ball cat toys with a bell inside! I will chase it so fast, then hold it in my mouth and walk around claiming my victory. Just try it while visiting The House of Mews, you'll see! Approx. DOB is 4/5/11.
Siblings are Mikey, Marty, Macy, Mae, Marie; mother is Maude. Approx. DOB is 5/11/11.

Marie is a sweet kitty who is happy to see you every time. She loves to just flop on the ground at your feet to get a belly rub. She loves to be helld, sit on your lap, and will reward you with purrs. Siblings are Mikey, Marty, Macy, Mae, Max; mother is Maude. Approx. DOB is 5/11/11.

All these boys! I'm the only female! I'm Rahab. I am the most mature of the group. I love to play but I am always high on my perch to watch the boys do their boy things. My brothers and I came to The House of Mews in June of 2011. We were fostered by a volunteer for over two months. We came in shy, covered in fleas and completely dirty. But we were cleaned up and brought to a nice comfy environment where we were socialized with a dog and two humans. Although I am still on the shy side, I am sweet and will let you love on me with time. I do love visitors, promise! Siblings are Abraham, Malachi, Potiphar, Ramesses, Titiana. Approx. DOB is 4/7/11.

breed.$t: Domestic Short Hair - buff and white

description.$t: Hi, I'm Abraham. I am a sophisticated kitty. I have a shy, sweet demeanor, much like my siblings. Give me a pat on the head and a scratch behind my ears and you have my attention. I like to relax and receive love. I will sit next to you when you sit on the floor. I want to be adopted by someone that will love me and kiss my forehead every day. That's what my foster mommy did. I have been socialized with small dogs, but young children may not be suitable. Siblings are Rahab, Malachi, Potiphar, Ramesses, Titiana. Approx. DOB is 4/7/11.

breed.$t: Domestic Short Hair - buff and white

description.$t: Malachi is my name. I love to play and I'm always in the mood for some canned treats. I will greet you at the door and rub all over your legs and follow you around. I will lay in your lap and purr while you pet me. I'm a big boy full of big love. Come meet me! Siblings are Abraham, Rahab, Potiphar, Ramesses, Titiana. Approx. DOB is 4/7/11.

My name is Titiana (formerly Titus, oops, I am a girl not a boy) and I am the smallest kitty in my litter. I have the sweetest face and I love to play with string. My brothers and sisters are a tight knit group. We spend a lot of time cuddling with each other. I'm a little shy, but I know with some good one-on-one time, my personality will shine. Siblings are Abraham, Malachi, Potiphar, Ramesses, Rahab. Approx. DOB is 4/7/11.

My siblings Nala, Carly and Tigger - and our mama Sparkle - were rescued from being put to sleep at the Memphis Animal Shelter. Actually, our mama was rescued before we were even born! We are a playful bunch and love to play together. I am the runt of the pack, and my siblings may think I'm weak just 'cause I'm smaller, but I hold my own! lthough I love to be held and pampered, ha!, I've got them all fooled. DOB is 4/28/11.

My siblings Nala, Ellie Mae and Tigger - and our mama Sparkle - were rescued from being put to sleep at the Memphis Animal Shelter. Actually, our mama was rescued before we were even born! We are a playful bunch and love to play together. I like to try and beat up on my brother Tigger before he gets me! He thinks he is big stuff being the only boy in the pack, but I can handle him! Oh, and aren't my markings pretty? DOB is 4/28/11.

I'm Katniss, named after the main character of "The Hunger Games" book (soon to be come a movie). I am a l-o-v-e-b-u-g! I crave your affection, love to be held, and really hope I get adopted soon! You've got to come meet me and see how sweet I am for yourself. I am high-energy with a little bit of sass too - that's called personality. Just like Katniss in The Hunger Games! Oh, and don't worry--that photo of me is a yawn, nothing more! I will lay on your lap and purr while you pet me too. I was rescued from being put to sleep at Memphis Animal Services. Siblings are Prim, Peeta and Juice; mother is Cherie. Approx. DOB is 3/16/11.

Titan is beautiful with crystal blue eyes. He's all white with beautiful brown markings and front declawed. However, he is a shy, aloof cat that is not a lap cat. He lays on The House of Mews counter right by the staff all the time, but his attitude sometimes can change abruptly. He will require a special adopter with patience and willingness to accept that he is not a cuddly lap cat and help work with his shyness and temperment. Titan probably needs to be an only cat or possibly one of two cats with another even tempered male. He was however photographed wearing a Santa hat and beard - although I am not sure how willingly... Approx. DOB is 9-5-05.

Merle, who was abandoned all alone, is a handsome ginger boy looking for love. Merle is sweet and playful, and will greet you at the door and rub all over your legs and follow you around. He will lay in your lap and purr while you pet him. At only 1 year old, he is still part kitten and part adult, why not let him grow up with you? Approx. DOB is 7/12/11.

I was found at a movie theater in Bartlett when I was 2 months old. I was scared and hungry, and hiding in the bushes so those big cars wouldn't run over me. I am a laid-back kitty who is very sweet and will show affection to those who show affection to me. I sometimes like to play with my kitty friend, CeCe. Approx. DOB is 10/13/08.

I was found in a trailer park where some kids were being mean to me. Not all kids are brought up right, I say. I am very affectionate, energetic and playful, and a little frisky too. I like to ride on your shoulders, like a parrot. I am a sweetheart who loves to be held. Awww! I will seek you out when you come visit The House of Mews, and I like to be in the middle of everything. I just want to be near you! And enough can't be said about a cat that will allow you to put this holiday decoration on me! Approx. DOB is 10/13/08.

Meet Elvis! This handsome (and big!) man is a hunka hunka Burning Love! I bet you Can't Help Falling in Love...he will be a Mess of Blues without you! Elvis is a sweet guy who likes attention and to be petted. He weighs nearly 20 pounds and is front declawed. Age currently unknown.

I'm Sarah Jane! I am looking for my forever home. Life hasn't always been easy for me. A nice lady rescued me when I was 8 weeks old. When I went to live with her, someone had hurt me bad. I had broken ribs and I was sad. This nice lady took care of me and now I am healthy, strong and affectionate and looking for someone to love me forever and always...could it be you? Approx. I am Imagine, named after a vegan restaurant in our neighborhood. My kittens and I were rescued from a local kill shelter. Yeah I know the story, fluffy long-haired kittens always get adopted first over shorter-haired black "old" cats. Hmph! You really need to come see what I am all about and put those black cat superstitions to rest! Come on, I am affectionate and only around 2 years old - that is pretty young in cat years. Approx. DOB is 2/23/10.

Bobbi is an affectionate kitten rescued from a local kill shelter. You can't tell from the photo but she's a super cute bobtail. She is talkative and wants to be friends with YOU! Approx. DOB is 12/1/11.

I'm Bettye, a pretty long-haired cat with NO TAIL! No one knows why I don't have one... I may have been born that way or perhaps something happened to it? I can't remember.
